🌸 MCR Activity Template

Activity Title: Watercolor Rainbow

Age Group: 2-12 years

Difficulty: easy

Category(s): 2-3 Years: sensory exploration, 4-5 years: motor coordination, 6-12 years: color mixing and painting techniques. 

Overview: 
Materials: Watercolors, brushes, and watercolor paper.
Instructions: paint a rainbow using the three primary colors: red, yellow, and blue.Then let's mix these primary colors to
 to create secondary colors: orange (red + yellow), green (yellow + blue), and purple (blue + red). 
Learning Goals: Learning relation between primery and secondary colors

Adapt I: younger children might use fingers or little sponge to paint, older can use a brush o thin brush to stimulate thin motor skills or specific paintin 

 
Monserrat's Tip: glue elements like rice or small leaves prior to the painting part in case you want to play with texture too 
Safety Notes (if needed): if adding elements for texture always makd sure to supervise your children, these to prevent asfixiation or swaloing objects


